.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH schedule 1  "schedule " 
.SH NAME
schedule \- Show or update synchronization schedules
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBschedule\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Show or update synchronization schedules
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
schedule\-set(1)
Update the global schedule
.TP
schedule\-folder(1)
Set schedule overrides for a named folder
.TP
schedule\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
